#* {{RQ:Manyoshu|5|840}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man5Yos.html#840 here]
#*: {{ja-usex|sort=うめ|m=波流楊那宜 可豆良尓乎利志 '''烏梅'''能波奈 多礼可有可倍志 佐加豆岐能倍尓|m_kana=はるやなぎ かづらにをりし '''うめ'''のはな たれかうかべし さかづきのへに|[[春%柳]]かづらに折りし'''梅'''の花%誰か浮かべし[[酒坏]]の上に|はる%やなぎ かづら に をりし '''うめ''' の はな% たれ か うかべし さかづき の へ に|'''Plum blossoms''', picked to make garlands like willows, who will float you in his cup?<ref>{{cite-book|1982|Paula Doe|author2={{w|Ōtomo no Yakamochi|Yakamochi Ōtomo}}|A Warbler's Song in the Dusk: The Life and Work of Ōtomo Yakamochi (718-785)|edition=illustrated|publisher=University of California Press|isbn=0-5200-4346-4|page=32}}</ref>}}
#* {{RQ:Shuishu|1|15}}
#*: {{ja-usex|我が宿の'''梅'''の立ち枝や見えつらむ思ひのほかに君が来ませる|わが やど の '''うめ''' の たち-え や みえつらむ おもひ の ほか に きみ が きませる|rom=waga yado no '''ume''' no tachi-e ya mietsuran omoi no hoka ni kimi ga kimaseru|Is it that the young branch tips, of the '''plum tree''' in my garden have come into view? For unexpectedly my lord, you have been moved to visit.<ref>{{cite-book|2014|Sugawara no Takasue no Musume|author2=Sonja Arntzen|author3=Moriyuki Ito|The Sarashina Diary: A Woman's Life in Eleventh-Century Japan|series=Translations from the Asian Classics|edition=illustrated, reprint|publisher=Columbia University Press|isbn=0-2315-3745-X|page=111}}</ref>}}
